TITLE: Polling for Events with SDL_PollEvent in C
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use SDL_PollEvent to process the event queue within a game loop. It polls for events until the queue is empty, then updates the game state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_PollEvent.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
while (game_is_still_running) {
    SDL_Event event;
    while (SDL_PollEvent(&event)) {  // poll until all events are handled!
        // decide what to do with this event.
    }

    // update game state, draw the current frame
}
```

