TITLE: Detecting Specific Key Presses with SDL_Keycode in SDL3 (C)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to detect specific key presses using SDL_Keycode, focusing on the symbol printed on the key, like the Escape key. It continuously polls for keydown events and checks if the pressed key matches SDLK_ESCAPE. Dependencies include SDL3.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/BestKeyboardPractices.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
/* sit in a loop forever until the user presses Escape. */
bool quit_the_app = false;
while (!quit_the_app) {
    SDL_Event e;
    while (SDL_PollEvent(&e)) {
        /* user has pressed a key? */
        if (e.type == SDL_EVENT_KEY_DOWN) {
            /* the pressed key was Escape? */
            if (e.key.key == SDLK_ESCAPE) {
                quit_the_app = true;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

