TITLE: Define SDL_DropEvent struct in C
DESCRIPTION: Defines the SDL_DropEvent structure, which is used to represent events related to dropping text or files into an SDL window. It includes fields for event type, timestamp, window ID, coordinates, source application, and the dropped data. This structure is available since SDL 3.2.0 and is located in SDL3/SDL_events.h.
