DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create an OpenGL context using SDL_GL_CreateContext. It first creates an SDL window with the SDL_WINDOW_OPENGL flag. Then, it creates an OpenGL context associated with that window. Finally, it shows basic OpenGL calls and destroys the context when done.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_GL_CreateContext.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
// Window mode MUST include SDL_WINDOW_OPENGL for use with OpenGL.
SDL_Window *window = SDL_CreateWindow(
    "SDL3/OpenGL Demo", 640, 480, 
    SDL_WINDOW_OPENGL|SDL_WINDOW_RESIZABLE);

// Create an OpenGL context associated with the window.
SDL_GLContext glcontext = SDL_GL_CreateContext(window);

// now you can make GL calls.
glClearColor(0,0,0,1);
glClear(GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);
SDL_GL_SwapWindow(window);

// Once finished with OpenGL functions, the SDL_GLContext can be destroyed.
SDL_GL_DestroyContext(glcontext);  
```

