TITLE: SDL_bsearch Example Usage in C
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use SDL_bsearch to search for an element in a sorted array of structs using a custom comparison function. It defines a struct `data`, a comparison function `compare`, and an array `values`, and then uses `SDL_bsearch` to find an element in `values`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_bsearch.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
typedef struct {
    int key;
    const char *string;
} data;

int SDLCALL compare(const void *a, const void *b)
{
    const data *A = (const data *)a;
    const data *B = (const data *)b;

    if (A->n < B->n) {
        return -1;
    } else if (B->n < A->n) {
        return 1;
    } else {
        return 0;
    }
}

data values[] = {
    { 1, "first" }, { 2, "second" }, { 3, "third" }
};
data key = { 2, NULL };

data *result = SDL_bsearch(&key, values, SDL_arraysize(values), sizeof(values[0]), compare);
```

