TITLE: SDL Event Filter for Mobile Devices in C
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use an SDL event filter to catch mobile-specific events immediately. It sets up a filter that checks for `SDL_APP_WILLENTERBACKGROUND` and frees resources to prevent the OS from terminating the application. `SDL_AddEventWatch` adds the filter to the event processing system.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL2/MigrationGuide.md#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
int SDLCALL myEventFilter(void *userdata, SDL_Event * event)
{
    if (event->type == SDL_APP_WILLENTERBACKGROUND) {
        // free up resources, DON'T DRAW ANY MORE until you're in the foreground again!
    }
    // etc
    return 1;
}

// somewhere near startup...

// this calls myEventFilter(data, event) as soon as event is generated.
SDL_AddEventWatch(myEventFilter, data);
```

