TITLE: SDL_qsort_r Usage Example
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use `SDL_qsort_r` to sort an array of structs based on a key, with the sorting order (increasing or decreasing) passed as user data to the comparison function. It defines an enum for sorting methods, a struct containing a key and a string, and a comparison function that utilizes the user data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_qsort_r.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
typedef enum {
    sort_increasing,
    sort_decreasing,
} sort_method;

typedef struct {
    int key;
    const char *string;
} data;

int SDLCALL compare(const void *userdata, const void *a, const void *b)
{
    sort_method method = (sort_method)(uintptr_t)userdata;
    const data *A = (const data *)a;
    const data *B = (const data *)b;

    if (A->key < B->key) {
        return (method == sort_increasing) ? -1 : 1;
    } else if (B->key < A->key) {
        return (method == sort_increasing) ? 1 : -1;
    } else {
        return 0;
    }
}

data values[] = {
    { 3, "third" }, { 1, "first" }, { 2, "second" }
};

SDL_qsort_r(values, SDL_arraysize(values), sizeof(values[0]), compare, (const void *)(uintptr_t)sort_increasing);
```

