TITLE: SDL_GPURenderStateDesc Structure Definition in C
DESCRIPTION: Defines the structure SDL_GPURenderStateDesc, which describes the GPU render state, including fragment shader, sampler bindings, storage textures, and storage buffers. The structure is intended to be initialized using SDL_INIT_INTERFACE(). It is available since SDL 3.4.0 and used with SDL_CreateGPURenderState.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_GPURenderStateDesc.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
typedef struct SDL_GPURenderStateDesc
{
    Uint32 version;                 /**< the version of this interface */

    SDL_GPUShader *fragment_shader; /**< The fragment shader to use when this render state is active */

