TITLE: Emscripten Main Loop Replacement in C
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet showcases the Emscripten-compatible main loop. It includes checks for the game's running state and deinitializes resources when the game is no longer running. The `emscripten_cancel_main_loop` function is used to terminate the application in Emscripten environments, while `exit(0)` is used in non-Emscripten environments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/README/emscripten.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
static void mainloop(void)   /* this will run often, possibly at the monitor's refresh rate */
{
    if (!game_is_still_running) {
        deinitialize_the_game();
        #ifdef __EMSCRIPTEN__
        emscripten_cancel_main_loop();  /* this should "kill" the app. */
        #else
        exit(0);
        #endif
    }

    check_for_new_input();
    think_about_stuff();
    draw_the_next_frame();
}

void main(void)
{
    initialize_the_game();
    #ifdef __EMSCRIPTEN__
    emscripten_set_main_loop(mainloop, 0, 1);
    #else
    while (1) { mainloop(); }
    #endif
}
```

