TITLE: Determine if SDL_PixelFormat is Indexed (C)
DESCRIPTION: This macro checks if a given SDL_PixelFormat is an indexed format. It uses SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC and SDL_PIXELTYPE to determine the format type and returns true if it is indexed, false otherwise.  The macro double-evaluates its parameter, so avoid side effects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_INDEXED.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
#define SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_INDEXED(format)   \
    (!SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format) && \
     ((SDL_PIXELTYPE(format) == SDL_PIXELTYPE_INDEX1) || \
      (SDL_PIXELTYPE(format) == SDL_PIXELTYPE_INDEX2) || \
      (SDL_PIXELTYPE(format) == SDL_PIXELTYPE_INDEX4) || \
      (SDL_PIXELTYPE(format) == SDL_PIXELTYPE_INDEX8)))
```

