TITLE: Defining SDL_PowerState Enum in C
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines the SDL_PowerState enumeration in C. It specifies the possible states of the system's power supply, including unknown, on battery, no battery, charging, and charged. This enum is part of the SDL library and resides in the SDL_power.h header file. It allows applications to determine the current power state of the system.
