TITLE: SDL_BYTESPERPIXEL Macro Definition in C
DESCRIPTION: This macro determines the bytes per pixel of a given SDL_PixelFormat. It checks if the format is a FourCC format and calculates the bytes per pixel accordingly. Note that the parameter is double-evaluated, so avoid side-effects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_BYTESPERPIXEL.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
#define SDL_BYTESPERPIXEL(format) \
    (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format) ? \
        ((((format) == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_YUY2) || \
          ((format) == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_UYVY) || \
          ((format) == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_YVYU) || \
          ((format) == SDL_PIXELFORMAT_P010)) ? 2 : 1) : (((format) >> 0) & 0xFF))
```

