TITLE: Enumerating Joysticks with SDL_GetJoysticks in C
DESCRIPTION: This C code snippet demonstrates how to enumerate connected joysticks using the SDL_GetJoysticks function. It initializes the joystick subsystem, retrieves a list of joystick instance IDs, iterates through the list to obtain joystick names and paths, and then logs the information before quitting the joystick subsystem. The function SDL_GetJoysticks() returns an array of `SDL_JoystickID` and the number of joysticks. Remember to free the allocated memory with `SDL_free` after use.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/README/migration.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
{
    if (SDL_InitSubSystem(SDL_INIT_JOYSTICK)) {
        int i, num_joysticks;
        SDL_JoystickID *joysticks = SDL_GetJoysticks(&num_joysticks);
        if (joysticks) {
            for (i = 0; i < num_joysticks; ++i) {
                SDL_JoystickID instance_id = joysticks[i];
                const char *name = SDL_GetJoystickNameForID(instance_id);
                const char *path = SDL_GetJoystickPathForID(instance_id);

                SDL_Log("Joystick %" SDL_PRIu32 ": %s%s%s VID 0x%.4x, PID 0x%.4x",
                        instance_id, name ? name : "Unknown", path ? ", " : "", path ? path : "", SDL_GetJoystickVendorForID(instance_id), SDL_GetJoystickProductForID(instance_id));
            }
            SDL_free(joysticks);
        }
        SDL_QuitSubSystem(SDL_INIT_JOYSTICK);
    }
}
```

