TITLE: U16 to S16 Audio Conversion
DESCRIPTION: This C code snippet demonstrates an in-place conversion from unsigned 16-bit (Uint16) audio data to signed 16-bit (Sint16) audio data.  It iterates through the buffer, XORing each unsigned 16-bit value with 0x8000 to effectively convert it to a signed representation. The buffer size remains unchanged after the conversion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/README/migration.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
/* this converts the buffer in-place. The buffer size does not change. */
Sint16 *audio_ui16_to_si16(Uint16 *buffer, const size_t num_samples)
{
    size_t i;
    const Uint16 *src = buffer;
    Sint16 *dst = (Sint16 *) buffer;

    for (i = 0; i < num_samples; i++) {
        dst[i] = (Sint16) (src[i] ^ 0x8000);
    }

    return dst;
}
```

