TITLE: Polling SDL Events in C
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use SDL_PollEvent to retrieve events from the event queue within a while loop.  It then uses a switch statement to handle different event types, specifically looking for SDL_MOUSEMOTION events and logging the mouse position.  If the queue is empty, the while loop exits and a log message is printed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL2/SDL_Event.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
while (SDL_PollEvent(&test_event)) {
  switch (test_event.type) {
    case SDL_MOUSEMOTION:
      SDL_Log("We got a motion event.");
      SDL_Log("Current mouse position is: (%d, %d)", test_event.motion.x, test_event.motion.y);
      break;
    default:
      SDL_Log("Unhandled Event!");
      break;
  }
}
SDL_Log("Event queue empty.");
```

