TITLE: Defining SDL_FOURCC Macro in C
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines the SDL_FOURCC macro, which takes four ASCII characters as input and combines them into a 32-bit unsigned integer. Each character is cast to Uint8 to ensure only the least significant byte is used, then cast to Uint32 and bit-shifted to its correct position in the resulting integer. The macro is used to create a unique identifier from four characters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_FOURCC.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
#define SDL_FOURCC(A, B, C, D) \
    ((SDL_static_cast(Uint32, SDL_static_cast(Uint8, (A))) << 0) | \
     (SDL_static_cast(Uint32, SDL_static_cast(Uint8, (B))) << 8) | \
     (SDL_static_cast(Uint32, SDL_static_cast(Uint8, (C))) << 16) | \
     (SDL_static_cast(Uint32, SDL_static_cast(Uint8, (D))) << 24))
```

