TITLE: SDL_NET_VERSION_ATLEAST Definition in C
DESCRIPTION: This macro checks if the compiled SDL_net version is at least the specified version (X.Y.Z). It compares the major, minor, and micro versions to determine compatibility. The macro evaluates to true if the compiled version meets or exceeds the specified version.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3_net/SDL_NET_VERSION_ATLEAST.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
#define SDL_NET_VERSION_ATLEAST(X, Y, Z) \
    ((SDL_NET_MAJOR_VERSION >= X) && \
     (SDL_NET_MAJOR_VERSION > X || SDL_NET_MINOR_VERSION >= Y) && \
     (SDL_NET_MAJOR_VERSION > X || SDL_NET_MINOR_VERSION > Y || SDL_NET_MICRO_VERSION >= Z))
```

