TITLE: Setting up sysroot for Cross-Compilation
DESCRIPTION: Sets up the sysroot environment required for cross-compilation.  This involves exporting the SYSROOT path, mounting the Raspbian image, copying files, and installing qemu for ARM emulation. Includes binding /dev, /proc, and /sys.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL2/README/raspberrypi.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
export SYSROOT=/opt/rpi-sysroot
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo kpartx -a -v <path_to_raspbian_image>.img
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo mount -o loop /dev/mapper/loop0p2 /mnt
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo cp -r /mnt $SYSROOT
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo apt-get install qemu binfmt-support qemu-user-static
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo cp /usr/bin/qemu-arm-static $SYSROOT/usr/bin
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo mount --bind /dev $SYSROOT/dev
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo mount --bind /proc $SYSROOT/proc
```

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
sudo mount --bind /sys $SYSROOT/sys
```

