TITLE: Defining SDL_enabled_assert Macro in C
DESCRIPTION: This code defines the SDL_enabled_assert macro in C, which is used to perform assertions. When the condition is false, it calls SDL_ReportAssertion to handle the assertion and provides options to retry, break, or continue.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/SDL_enabled_assert.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
#define SDL_enabled_assert(condition) \
    do { \
        while ( !(condition) ) { \
            static struct SDL_AssertData sdl_assert_data = { 0, 0, #condition, 0, 0, 0, 0 }; \
            const SDL_AssertState sdl_assert_state = SDL_ReportAssertion(&sdl_assert_data, SDL_FUNCTION, SDL_FILE, SDL_LINE); \
            if (sdl_assert_state == SDL_ASSERTION_RETRY) { \
                continue; /* go again. */ \
            } else if (sdl_assert_state == SDL_ASSERTION_BREAK) { \
                SDL_AssertBreakpoint(); \
            } \
            break; /* not retrying. */ \
        } \
    } while (SDL_NULL_WHILE_LOOP_CONDITION)
```

