TITLE: Handling NSApplicationDelegate Open File (Objective-C)
DESCRIPTION: This Objective-C snippet handles the SDL_DROPFILE event when opening files in a macOS application. It checks the SDL_DROPFILE event state and pushes a SDL_DROPFILE event with the filename to SDL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL2/README/macos.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: objc
CODE:
```
- (BOOL)application:(NSApplication *)theApplication openFile:(NSString *)filename
{
    if (SDL_GetEventState(SDL_DROPFILE) == SDL_ENABLE) {
        SDL_Event event;
        event.type = SDL_DROPFILE;
        event.drop.file = SDL_strdup([filename UTF8String]);
        return (SDL_PushEvent(&event) > 0);
    }

    return NO;
}
```

