TITLE: Cross-compiling for armeabi-v7a architecture
DESCRIPTION: Cross-compiles the project for the `armeabi-v7a` architecture, which supports more advanced ARM processors. Uses specific compiler and linker flags to target this architecture and ensure compatibility, including flags for VFPv3-D16 and Cortex-A8 optimization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/Android.md#_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
mkdir cross-android-v7a/ && cd cross-android-v7a/
# .o: -march=armv5te -mtune=xscale -msoft-float -mthumb  =>  -march=armv7-a -mfpu=vfpv3-d16 -mfloat-abi=softfp -mthumb
# .so: -march=armv7-a -Wl,--fix-cortex-a8
CFLAGS="-g -O2 -march=armv7-a -mfpu=vfpv3-d16 -mfloat-abi=softfp -mthumb" LFDLAGS="-march=armv7-a -Wl,--fix-cortex-a8" \
  ../configure --host=arm-linux-androideabi \
  ...
```

