TITLE: SDL_MIXER_VERSION_ATLEAST Macro Definition in C
DESCRIPTION: This macro checks if the SDL_mixer version is at least X.Y.Z. It compares the major, minor, and patch versions against the provided arguments. The macro relies on SDL_MIXER_MAJOR_VERSION, SDL_MIXER_MINOR_VERSION, and SDL_MIXER_PATCHLEVEL being defined during compilation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL2_mixer/SDL_MIXER_VERSION_ATLEAST.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
#define SDL_MIXER_VERSION_ATLEAST(X, Y, Z) \
    ((SDL_MIXER_MAJOR_VERSION >= X) && \
