TITLE: Defining IMG_Animation Structure in C
DESCRIPTION: This C code snippet defines the `IMG_Animation` structure, which is used to store data for animated images within the SDL_image library. It includes the width and height of the frames, the number of frames, an array of SDL_Surface pointers to each frame, and an array of delays (in milliseconds) for each frame. This structure is specifically used for animated GIFs and WEBP images.
