TITLE: SDL_MIN_SINT16 Macro Definition (C)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the SDL_MIN_SINT16 macro as the minimum value for a Sint16, which is -32768. This macro provides a constant expression to represent the minimum value for a signed 16-bit integer in SDL3 applications. It's vital for checking lower bounds and maintaining data integrity in SDL3-based C code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/libsdl-org/sdlwiki/blob/main/SDL3/Sint16.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
